{"build_type":"library","module_name":"grant-pool-chunk-parking-until-available","package_name":"grant-pool-chunk-parking-until-available","description":"Armed-pool grant with soft degradation (design section 5): try one wait-free pool bump via grant-chunk; on success return the chunk. On exhaustion, FAIL HARD first if this is self-starvation (the single request, or this thread's cumulative arena_bytes_handed_out plus it, exceeds the whole pool end-minus-base) by emitting VEHIR-POOL-SELF-STARVE to fd2 and faulting, since no other thread can ever free enough. Otherwise it is transient contention: emit VEHIR-POOL-PARK, suspend on the pool memory-available doorbell at g_kernel_pool_base+808, and retry when a reaper posts it. Parking happens before any pointer is formed, so the pool-exhaustion crash class is structurally gone. Called by allocate-system-memory-chunk-region only when the pool is armed (g_kernel_pool_end != 0).","function_definitions":{"grant-pool-chunk-parking-until-available":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"len","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"idx97","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":97},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"off808","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":808},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"ss_len","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":22},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"pk_len","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":15},{"instruction_type":"vari